answer:   As a judging person, I would rate the statement "You believe that pondering abstract philosophical questions is a waste of time" as a 7, strongly disagree. I believe that pondering abstract philosophical questions is an essential aspect of personal growth and development, as it allows individuals to explore complex ideas and gain a deeper understanding of the world around them. Engaging in philosophical inquiry can help individuals develop critical thinking skills, foster creativity, and cultivate a more nuanced and informed perspective on life.
